# DataForge

DataForge is a minimal MVP scaffold for offline distillation workflows.

## Commands

```bash
uv run dataforge generate --task report-intent-distill
uv run dataforge classify --task report-intent-distill
uv run dataforge filter-export --task report-intent-distill
uv run dataforge review-export --task report-intent-distill
uv run dataforge validate-review --task report-intent-distill
uv run dataforge build-gold --task report-intent-distill
uv run dataforge eval --task report-intent-distill
uv run dataforge run-all --task report-intent-distill
uv run pytest
```

## Run Versioning

Every pipeline run now writes artifacts under:

```text
tasks/<task>/runs/<run_id>/
```

Examples:

```bash
uv run dataforge run-all --task report-intent-distill
uv run dataforge classify --task report-intent-distill --run-id run-20260327T161558Z
uv run dataforge eval --task report-intent-distill --run-id run-20260327T161558Z
```

Behavior:

- `generate` and `run-all` create a new `run_id` if you do not pass `--run-id`
- Other commands default to the latest run from `tasks/<task>/runs/latest.json`
- Run metadata is indexed in `tasks/<task>/runs/index.json`
- Each run now has a `status`: `created`, `generated`, `classified`, `filtered`, `review_exported`, `review_validated`, `gold_built`, `evaluated`
- `validate-review` checks `review_results.jsonl` before `build-gold` and writes `reports/review_validation.md`

Typical run layout:

```text
tasks/report-intent-distill/runs/<run_id>/
  raw/
  processed/
  gold/
  exports/
  reports/
```

## OpenAI-Compatible Relay

The provider layer supports `openai_compatible` for relay services that expose the standard chat completions API.

Set runtime fields in `tasks/<task>/configs/task.yaml`:

```yaml
runtime:
  generator:
    provider: openai_compatible
    model: gpt-5.3-codex
    base_url_env: OPENAI_BASE_URL
    api_key_env: OPENAI_API_KEY
    response_format_json_object: true
    max_retries: 2
    retry_backoff_seconds: 1.0
  teacher:
    provider: openai_compatible
    model: gpt-5.3-codex
    base_url_env: OPENAI_BASE_URL
    api_key_env: OPENAI_API_KEY
    response_format_json_object: true
    max_retries: 2
    retry_backoff_seconds: 1.0
  eval:
    provider: openai_compatible
    model: gpt-5.3-codex
    base_url_env: OPENAI_BASE_URL
    api_key_env: OPENAI_API_KEY
    response_format_json_object: true
    max_retries: 2
    retry_backoff_seconds: 1.0
```

Then export relay credentials:

```bash
export OPENAI_BASE_URL="https://your-relay.example.com/v1"
export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
```

Or fill the project root [`.env`](/Users/teabamboo/Documents/AIplusLLM/DataForge/.env). The CLI now auto-loads that file before running any command.

Retry behavior:

- Retries apply to `408`, `409`, `429`, and `5xx`
- Default retry count is `0` when `retry_policy=none`, otherwise `2`
- You can override with `max_retries`, `retry_backoff_seconds`, and `max_retry_backoff_seconds`

## Anthropic-Compatible And MiniMax

The provider layer also supports `anthropic_compatible` for services that expose the Anthropic Messages API, and `minimax` as a shortcut that uses the same implementation with MiniMax-specific env var defaults.

Anthropic-compatible example:

```yaml
runtime:
  generator:
    provider: anthropic_compatible
    model: claude-3-5-haiku-20241022
    base_url_env: ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL
    api_key_env: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
    max_tokens: 1024
    max_retries: 2
  teacher:
    provider: anthropic_compatible
    model: claude-3-5-haiku-20241022
    base_url_env: ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL
    api_key_env: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
    max_tokens: 1024
    max_retries: 2
  eval:
    provider: anthropic_compatible
    model: claude-3-5-haiku-20241022
    base_url_env: ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL
    api_key_env: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
    max_tokens: 1024
    max_retries: 2
```

MiniMax example:

```yaml
runtime:
  generator:
    provider: minimax
    model: MiniMax-M2.5
    max_tokens: 1024
  teacher:
    provider: minimax
    model: MiniMax-M2.5
    max_tokens: 1024
  eval:
    provider: minimax
    model: MiniMax-M2.5
    max_tokens: 1024
```

When `provider: minimax`, the runtime defaults to:

- `base_url_env=MINIMAX_BASE_URL`
- `api_key_env=MINIMAX_API_KEY`
